DENNILTON police in Mpumalanga have launched a manhunt for three dangerous inmates who escaped while being transported from Groblersdal to Witbank Prison at about 11am on Wednesday, 25 January. According to Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo, the three awaiting trial prisoners – Michael Masimula, Mahlatse Matebane and Lovemore Moshui aged between 20 and 40 – appeared in the Groblersdal Magistrates Court on Tuesday, 24 January. Mojapelo said the three inmates were being transported to prison together with three other prisoners. He said the dangerous trio escaped next to Moutse Mall in the Dennilton policing area. REGISTER TO COMMENT! “The escapees appeared on charges of murder, rape, armed robberies, cash-in-transit heists and possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. The Provincial Limpopo police commissioner, Lieutenant-General Thembi Hadebe, has ordered that the escapees be hunted down and brought back to where they belong,” Mojapelo said in a statement. Mojapelo said circumstances surrounding the escape are still being investigated, adding that the suspects are considered dangerous and people are cautioned not to approach them, but must call the police instead. Anyone with information is urged to contact Lieutenant-Colonel Richard Boshomane on 079 894 5501, or the CrimeStop at 08600 10111.